    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1237"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1237">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/1892</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spring Rice</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                    <gloss type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I beg to acknowledge your
                    informal letter of the 27th instant, in which you bring to my attention certain
                    information in your possession relative to the operations of British warships in
                    the Pacific and in particular the report that the British steamship <hi
                        rend="italic">Bellerophon</hi> coaled His Majesty’s ship <hi rend="italic"
                        >Rainbow</hi> on the 27th of February within a mile of Anacapa Island.</p>
                <p>I am bringing this matter at once to the attention of my Government and shall
                    take pleasure in communicating further with you upon the subject as soon as I am
                    in a position to do so.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cecil Spring Rice</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
